                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13714608" author="isudana" created="Sun, 21 Jul 2013 02:21:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch prevents the message getting built always when endpoint format is set to &quot;rest&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Now the message get built only if there is a content aware mediator is present in the mediation flow.&lt;br/&gt;
If there is a message format conversion from SOAP to REST happens within the mediation flow, we usually set the messageType property which is a content-aware property.&lt;br/&gt;
So it is safe not to built message always when endpoint format is set to &quot;rest&quot; and allow rest passthrough scenario.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13714770" author="hiranya" created="Sun, 21 Jul 2013 18:53:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied. Thanks Isuru for the contribution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
